sp.p:
My thoughts are as black as your beard, my fortunes as ill proportioned as your legs; 
and all the powers of my mind, as leaden as your wit, and as dusty as your face is 
swarthy.

Pew, thou jestest. In good sadness, I will have a looking glass nailed to the the testern of the bed, 
that I may see when I sleep, whether it is so, or not; 
take heed you lie not: go to, take heed you lie not.

Up on his shoulders, that 
is the fittest place for it. If it be not as fit as if it were made for them; 
say, Balurdo, thou art a sot, an ass.

No? well, let me have a good massy ring, with your 
own poesy graven in it, that must sing a small 
treble, word for word, thus;
